des to detect linear position one cathode one xxxxx xxxxx light xxxxx divider output xxxxx xxxxx xxxxx one two xxxxx gnd xxxxx xxxxx anode xxxxx cathode two two if the dot of light from the led is the only source of light then the position of the projection is given by this circuit regardless of the level of illumina tion the divider is used to normalize relative to total received power when this circuit is used in the presence of other sources of light then the way of tuning to it is to sample for a few msec the background signal light the led for an equal time and sample that signal separately the difference between the two is the position of the led hamamatsu photonics sells linear and two d lateral photoeffect detectors and they also sell the required signal processing electronics the ready made systems by selspot and others are not cheap lindholm l e and k e oberg an optoelectronic instrument for remote on line movement monitoring biotelemetry one nine four nine five one nine seven four woltring h j and e b marsolais opto electronic selspot gait measure ments in two and three dimensional space a preliminary report bull pros thetics research four six five two one nine eight zero most probably this technique can provide you with a much more accurate measurement than you need but i think that its simplicity beats scanning a quadrant detector with a pan tilt system until you reach zero difference david david prutchi hc one dt washington university campus box one one eight five one brookings drive st louis mo six three one three zero four eight nine nine